description: This issue translates Venom: Funeral Pyre #1, Venom: Deathtrap The Vault, and the Venom story from Web Of Spider-Man Annual #6, to Italian.

The soaring Sentinel of the Spaceways makes a Marvel Masterworks splash with his unmatched solo series, now in paperback. Illustrated by the master of man, menace, and motion, the one-and-only John Buscema, and featuring some of Stan Lee’s most inspired and socially charged scripts of the Silver Age, the adventures of Norrin Radd rank among the definitive tales of all Marveldom!

Not only will you be awed beyond imagination by the Surfer’s origin, you’ll also face alien invasions, be torn down to the depths of hell by the utterly evil Mephisto, struggle against the Stranger, and face galaxy-conquering barbarians set on the destruction of…well, everything!

Lest we forget what by many is considered the most beautifully rendered story in Marvel history, the Surfer’s tête à tête with the mighty Thor! These double-length stories of drama and despair are a must-have for any and every Marvelite, and to prove we mean it, we’re including the Surfer’s first-ever solo adventure from the pages of Fantastic Four Annual #5 as bonus!

Collecting Silver Surfer issues #1 to 6, Fantastic Four Annual #5 and Not Brand Echh #13, written by Stan Lee, pencilled by John Buscema and Jack Kirby, with cover artwork by John Buscema and Dean White.
name: Volume One

description:
Back-to-press and fully restored by popular demand! The world's favourite space-faring super hero in his continuing saga of anguish and adventure! He sacrificed himself to save his home world of Zenn-La from the planet-devouring menace Galactus, saving those he loved in exchange for a life of servitude as the Silver Surfer. Now, after disobeying his master, Norrin Radd is stranded on the planet Earth - forever removed from his love, Shalla-Bal, and from the beckoning spaceways!

A high point of epic adventure and lyrical drama, the Silver Surfer took the comic-book super hero to all-new heights. Using their ravaged protagonist as a lens through which they could comment on the social injustices of the era, Stan Lee and John Buscema turned the Surfer into the ultimate outsider archetype, reflecting the reader's world in his metallic skin. In these pages, the Surfer will face ghosts from beyond the grave seeking redemption, the horrors of war, the devious Mephisto, and mighty Marvel heroes including Spider-Man to the Human Torch and the Inhumans.

So what more do you need to know? Reserve that copy today, True Believer! Collecting the Silver Surfer issues #7 through to 18, written by Stan Lee and pencilled by John Buscema (who also provides the cover artwork) and Jack Kirby
name: Volume Two

description: Collects : X-Factor (1986) # 04 - Longshot (1985) # 04- Marvel Comics Presents (1988) # 35
After watching Teasure Island at the cinema Dennis, Gnasher and Rasher become pirates.
name: Desert Island Dennis
Black Diamond Detective Agency

description: After getting into trouble once again Minnies father decides she needs to learn some manners and culture and sends her to various classes like ballet dancing, pottery and singing.
name: The Minnie Lisa

description: Created by the titanic team of Stan Lee and Jack Kirby in the pages of The Fantastic Four, the Silver Surfer went on to become one of the most-beloved characters in all comicdom. Embodying the mind-blowing concepts of Kirby and Stan's socially conscious writing craft, the Surfer's stories expressed their creative vision in staggering and unique stories. Another talent would touch the character, however, granting him a soul-wrenching humanity that helped define him to this very day-the one and only, John Buscema! A master of the craft, Buscema's Silver Surfer is considered by many to be the peak of comic-book art. Now, the original adventures of the Silver Surfer are presented in one complete volume! Containing every story and letters page, restored and recolored to match the original issues, plus behind-the-scenes bonuses and critical essays, this book is the guaranteed way to get in on the character in the upcoming film, Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer! Collecting Silver Surfer #1-18.
name: Volume One

description: Where has the Captain America from the '50s been the past few months, and what part of our modern world has welcomed him? And what will Steve and Bucky do when an old enemy tries to become a revolutionary? Plus, Steve Rogers has returned, but Bucky Barnes is the current Captain America, and has come into his own in the role. Will there be two Captain Americas? Will Bucky go back to being the Winter Soldier? What will happen? Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA #602-605 and WHO WILL WIELD THE SHIELD? ONE-SHOT
name: Captain America: Two Americas

description: After missing out on buffalo Little Plum and Chiefy are forced to hunt bears to keep away the hunger pains. Though these bears are far to clever for the Smellyfeet tribe.
name: Um Brave Bear Hunter

description: One month later. Nick Fury's got an army. Hydra goes to war. Leviathan reveals itself. Things heat up and Young Gun Stefano Caselli returns to knock it out of the park! Also, the long-awaited origin of the mysterious HIVE, and we finally find out who the father of STONEWALL is. Collecting SECRET WARRIORS #11-16.
name: Secret Warriors: Wake the Beast

description: Dennis is desprate to prove Rasher is a better pet than Walters budgie. One problem though is Rasher is a big fat pig and can't fly like Walters Budgie. Dennis tricks Rasher into thinking the clouds are made of cream so he makes every attempt possible to reach the sky.
name: Pigasus The Flying Hog

description:
The nexus of LA vice and hip-hop life is @Large, an internet gaming cafe with a notorious recording studio upstairs. Everyone comes together in the gaming lounges of @Large--geeks, rappers, techno-ninjas, thugs, wannabes and undercover cops. The story revolves around a group of kids known as DNA as they attempt to navigate through the trials of adolescence, gain street fame and survive the ever-present threat of the underworld. When they encounter agents of the dark power behind the recording studio, the DNA crew finds themselves fighting for their lives...and for the very survival of their community.

----------

Who's Who in the L.A. Zoo?

Rust is a bugged-out graffiti artist with an anger management problem. True Epic is a battle hungry wannabe rapper who's not afraid of going up against the pros. Broke Rogers is an overexposed, commercial MC with a big record deal and an even bigger ego. And Skye is a blonde bombshell with a secret big enough to bring them all down. The fight for survival, street fame and respect begins and ends in the gaming lounges of the Internet café known as @Large.
name: Vol. 1

description:
General Blight and the other Super-villians of Great Britain are tired of their plans constantly being foiled by Bananaman so they head to the United States. Without a super-hero of their own America is helpless to stop the crime-wave untill Mervyn P. Wimpole, Bananamans number one fan in the U.S., decides to do something about it. Without any bananas Mervyn eats the next best thing, the yellow cactus of Texas, which turns him into Bananadan!
 
Only together can Bananaman and Bananadan defeat General Blight and his evil cronies.
name: Bananadan
Vol. 3

description:
For nearly a millennium, undead creatures have blended into a Europe heavy with religious dogma and intolerance. These beasts of the night allied themselves with factions of mortal men who aimed at shaking the foundations of the Catholic Church and freeing society from its strangling grip. But always were their true natures hidden, often even from even each other. The world was unable and unwilling to accept the existence of extra-mortal beings. A Midnight Opera is the story of two undead brothers Ein and Leroux DeLaLune, who are divided in this epic struggle and who are forced to reconcile their differences in the modern day to stop an open assault on mankind by the dissatisfied elements among the rest of the undead.

Volume 1 focuses on Ein, who fled his brethren in the early 19th century only to surface early in the 21st century as an underground goth metal sensation. But with his newfound fame comes the exposure that brings all the demons from his past. And the Ein who wanted simply to pursue a life of music and love will find that he may have no other choice but to forsake both and assume the weight of all salvation on his shoulders.
name: Vol. 1

description: Reunited under the direst of circumstances, the undead brothers Ein and Leroux Delalune rush to usher the rest of the immortals out of Paris. Meanwhile, the witch Elizabeth Bathory has second thoughts about her poisonous role in the peace the brothers have created. Will her doubts cause a rift between her and Victor Frankenstein, who wants to carry out her plan with a passionate fervor?
name: Vol. 2

description: The Order, under the draconian leadership of Cardinal LaCroix, closes in on Paris to exterminate the undead, and with them is the powerful lunatic Peter Stubbe. But a link between LaCroix and the Brothers DeLaLune might have a deeper effect on the outcome of the looming battle than the scores of soldiers on both sides ready to fight. Elizabeth and Leroux have a lot to talk about, and now that Dahlia knows Ein's secret, will she still love him?
name: Vol. 3

description: It's Rodeo time in Cactusville and every gunslinger, crook and outlaw is in town to lay claim to the prize money. It's up to Deputy Dan to keep the peace.
name: Rodeo Round up

description:
From the Creator of Pet Shop of Horrors and Kamen Tantei!

Kamishina has never really felt like a normal boy. At school, he prefers to lay low and not interact with the other kids. But all that changes when Kamishina discovers that he is the reincarnated spiritual ruler of the little-known country of Dhalashar. And on top of that, he has an intense spiritual sense that allows him to hear voices from beyond the grave, see visions, and soothe ghosts in their time of need. Living a normal life will just have to wait!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Garuda's Talons
  • Chapter 2: The Wandering Kingdom
  • Chapter 3: The Boy From the Rainy Day
  • Chapter 4: Assassins
  • Chapter 5: Father and Son
name: Vol. 1

description:
Fuuto's plastering across television has only brought him problems. The overnight celebrity now must help a friend he hasn't seen in five years escape his room. Not only that, the young ladies have taken a liking to him. And, one in particular, seems to be dead set on getting him! To make the situation worse, Naga's Third Assassin is tailing him on the class trip.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Behind the Door
  • Chapter 2: The Two Thrones
  • Chapter 3: The Third Assassin
  • Chapter 4: Labyrinth In the Capital
  • Chapter 5: Partner
name: Vol. 2

description:
With Valentine's Day just around the corner, Fuuto smells the love in the air. He plans a romantic interlude with Mayu in hopes of getting some sweet chocolate. But on his way to meet her, Yakuza's henchmen kidnap him! As Fuuto faces his final hour, he receives a rude awakening in his present life--and his past one.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Family
  • Chapter 2: Rivals
  • Chapter 3: Bride of God
  • Chapter 4: Kirin
  • Chapter 5: Blade of the Champion
  • The Genju Files #1
name: Vol. 3

description:
After a string of animal murders are discovered throughout town, Fuuto and his guardians vow to bring the killer to justice. But after the return of Sohki leads to a startling turn of events, the young king begins rethinking what justice really is. Also, what happens when Fuuto pays a visit to the mysterious new pet shop that just opened in Tokyo? Find out in this volume's bonus story starring Pet Shop of Horror's Count D!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: A Wordless Voice
  • Chapter 2: Bond of Fate
  • Chapter 3: Doorway To the Throne
  • Chapter 4: The Two Holy Knights
  • In the Mysterious Chinese Man's Shop
name: Vol. 4

description: Fuuto's classmate Eriko has to sneak out of town to escape the collection agency that has been harassing her family ever since her father disappeared, leaving behind a huge debt. Using his power, Fuuto locates Eriko's father--who is just about to commit suicide!
name: Vol. 5

description: Ibaraki, the Demoness, has finally appeared--but what effect will her presence have on the violence already taking place? And why do Fuuto's Guardian Beasts seem so familiar with her? She'll play a crucial role before this terrible day is done...but will she be a force for good or evil?
name: Vol. 6

description:
Kamishina is the reincarnated ruler of Dhalashar. He can hear voices from beyond the grave, see visions, and soothe ghosts... In this volume, Ohko tries to awaken a spirit known as the true king, but instead, Ohko causes a huge explosion, after which a mysterious boy appears from thin air...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: The Priestess of the King
  • Chapter 2: A Mysterious Boy
  • Chapter 3: A Troublesome Client
  • Chapter 4: Rika
  • Chapter 5: Operation: F
name: Vol. 7

description: Kamishima is the reincarnated ruler of Dhalashar. He can hear voices from beyond the grave, see visions and soothe ghosts... Now that the end of the world has been prevented, Fuuto must protect Mayu from her own parents and the world from a mysterious, never-before-seen beast who won’t answer to any of the guardians!
name: Vol. 8

description: Jackie Chan never has a dull moment. After finding a rare ancient talisman with unknown powers, he is recruited by an old friend into Section 13, a secret government agency. Jackie's mission: to travel around the world and capture the 12 magical talismans of the Chinese zodiac and keep them from the criminal group, The Dark Hand. In his spare time, Jackie must keep his young niece Jade out of trouble, but that's a full-time job in itself! Good thing Jackie, Jade and Uncle don't mind kicking a little butt to stay one step ahead of danger! Includes the episodes, 'The Dark Hand' and 'The Power Within.'
name: Enter the Dark Hand

description: An Archeologist found a shield and two sides are after it. The Dark Hand and Section 13. Jackie and Captain Black work together along with Jackie's niece and uncle to combat against the forces of darkness. This is the second of three of the Jackie Chan Adventures cine-manga.
name: Legend of the Zodiac

description:
Samurai Kokaku Sento likes peppers. Scratch that--he loves them. The only thing Kokaku likes better than eating a hot chili pepper is helping his father kick the butt of bad guys! With the help of his bespectacled friend Ento and cutie-pie girl of action Ran, Kokaku will take a bite out of crime--but not before biting a spicy pepper first!

Chapter Titles

  • 1st Subject: The Volume of Long Life
  • 2nd Subject: The Volume of the Dancing Crane
  • 3rd Subject: The Volume of the Crane and Turtle
  • 4th Subject: The Volume of the Unemployed
  • 5th Subject: The Volume of the Black Crane
  • Side Story: The Volume of the Wise Crane
name: Vol. 1

description:
Kokaku proves his temper’s as hot as his favorite chilies when he gets into a fight with Ento that just keeps escalating. Then things apparently mellow out when he and Tsumugi meet a mild-mannered fisherman with a hidden identity. But how long can the calm last when trouble follows our hero wherever he goes?

Chapter Titles

  • 6th Subject: Snow Crane
  • 7th Subject: Kakuga
  • 8th Subject: Saikaku
  • 9th Subject: Unkaku
name: Vol. 2

description: Nanako is the belle of her high school--just as long as she stays quiet. Once she shows her true self, guys' dreams are shattered because she is a tomboy! Meanwhile, Akira has the looks and brains--but his personality is so dull nobody notices him. But one day Nanako's grandfather comes up with crazy, life-altering invention and Nanako and Akira are forced to keep a very big secret: When they switch bodies with each other, will they ever want to go back?!
name: Vol. 1

description: Be careful what you wish for or you might just get it...and discover you like it! When Akira Uehara, overlooked because he doesn't open his mouth, and Nanako Momoi, looked over until she opens her mouth, switch bodies they find their new selves surprisingly comfortable. Unfortunately they're not the only ones. Akira and Nanako's pre-swap best friends are now drawn to them post-op. And they want to spend the night! These two will have to do more than just tango in this volume of Your & My Secret!
name: Vol. 2

description: With no intention of ever switching back, Momoi begins dating her pre-swap best friend, Shiina. Meanwhile, Akira's pre-swap best friend, Senbongi, continues to pursue him, making Akira even more devoted to regaining his own body. But when Senbongi overhears a conversation between Momoi and Akira and uncovers their secret, what will happen to them now that someone knows the truth?
name: Vol. 3

description: Senbongi is acting cold while Akira seems to be getting along with Shiina with no intentions of switching back. Akira gives Momoi the OK to go out with a guy (or at least hold hands!), rubbing in the fact that she has no feelings toward him. Fed up with it all, Momoi agrees to go out with Senbongi and discovers that, to his surprise, he actually kind of likes it!
name: Vol. 4

description: It's time for a school trip to chilly Hokkaido, full of hot springs, tasty food, and love hotels--the perfect excuse for two budding couples to get cozy and maybe even get busy! But as Shiina and Akira get closer and closer, Nanako fights with feelings of jealousy, in spite of her resolve to move on. Meanwhile, things with Senbongi are moving forward as well, complicating matters all the more--is he still just a best friend to Nanako, or...? And what happens when Akira's little sister starts falling for her newly-manly brother? Don't miss more crazy fun (and Nanako in a push-up bra!) in volume 5 of Your & My Secret!
name: Vol. 5
